results.name: Permutation of natural numbers: a(n) = A255551(A252460(n)).
comment: a(n) tells which number in array A255551, constructed from Lucky sieve, is at the same position where n is in array A083221, constructed from the sieve of Eratosthenes. As both arrays have A005843 (even numbers) as their topmost row, this permutation fixes all of them.
